[assistant] 抽取并记录信息: {"user_identity": "", "user_preference": "", "research_direction": "Corticosteroid treatment for CIDP", "filter_requirements": "randomised controlled trials (RCTs) or quasi-RCTs of treatment with any corticosteroid or adrenocorticotrophic hormone for CIDP, diagnosed by an internationally accepted definition.", "rejection_reasons": "", "other_info": "The review was first published in 2001 and last updated in 2015. It assessed the effects of corticosteroid treatment for CIDP compared to placebo or no treatment, and compared different corticosteroid regimens. The search methods included Cochrane Neuromuscular Specialised Register, Cochrane Central Register of Controlled Trials, MEDLINE, Embase, clinical trials registries. Selection criteria were RCTs or quasi-RCTs with any corticosteroid or adrenocorticotrophic hormone for CIDP, diagnosed by an internationally accepted definition. Two authors extracted data and assessed risk of bias independently. The primary outcome was change in disability, measured after 12 weeks, with side effects as secondary outcomes. GRADE approach was used for strength of evidence assessment. One RCT comparing prednisone with no treatment did not measure the primary outcome; another double-blind RCT comparing dexamethasone and prednisolone reported none of prespecified outcomes. Quality of evidence varied from very low to limited, with some moderate or low quality. Side effects were common but varied between regimens. The efficacy of dexamethasone was similar to prednisolone, though moon facies and sleeplessness were less common in dexamethasone group. Further research is needed to identify factors predicting response."}
